```
★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────
TypeScript's structural type system means optional chaining (`?.`) on 
a property that doesn't exist in the type definition still errors — the 
compiler doesn't know the property exists to make it optional. The fix is 
a narrow cast that exposes only the needed surface, keeping the type 
assertion scope minimal and self-documenting.
─────────────────────────────────────────────────
```
